### What version of Foundry are you on?

forge 0.2.0 (950d863 2023-10-25T11:49:15.075206396Z)

### What command(s) is the bug in?

_No response_

### Operating System

Linux

### Describe the bug

```solidity
function test_minimal() public {
    assertTrue(false);
    vm.expectRevert();
}

// [FAIL. Reason: Call did not revert as expected]
```

Given the toy example above, one may expect something like `Assertion failed` because of  `assertTrue(false);` but instead `Call did not revert as expected` emitted.

```solidity
function test_minimal() public {
    vm.expectRevert();
    _itReverts();
    this._call();
}

function _itReverts() internal {
    // Arithmetic over/underflow
    type(uint256).max + 1;
}

function _call() external {
    // nop
}

// [PASS] test_minimal() (gas: 3178)
```

Given another example, one may expect something like `[FAIL. Reason: Arithmetic over/underflow]` but instead it looks like the `vm.expectRevert` inspects the test function call itself (just my guess) and silently passes the test. With no `this._call();` it works in the same way.
